Description: Fragment of flattened handle from a Knidian pottery transport amphora. Clay medium pink-buff; some mica. Circular stamp with amphora symbol and Greek inscription.
Type series: KT595 (Virginia Grace's unpublished K(nidian) T(ype) series)
Curator's comments: Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p.55, 31 (now broken) Name, Ermogenes
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0323)
